# Database Layer

Read `docs/IMPLEMENTATION_SPEC.md` §6 for complete schemas.

## PostgreSQL Patterns
- Connection pool: max 20 connections, idle timeout 30s
- All SQL in named query files (`src/db/queries/*.ts`), never inline
- Use parameterized queries ($1, $2) — never string interpolation
- Use transactions for multi-table operations (especially epoch transitions)
- UPSERT pattern (`ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE`) for idempotent writes

## Key Tables
- `posts`: uri (PK), cid, author_did, text, reply_root, reply_parent, langs, has_media, created_at, indexed_at, **deleted** (boolean, default false)
- `post_engagements`: post_uri (FK), likes, reposts, replies (counters updated by handlers)
- `social_graph`: follower_did, followed_did, created_at, deleted
- `post_scores`: post_uri, epoch_id, all 5 component scores + weights + weighted values + total_score + JSONB details. UNIQUE(post_uri, epoch_id)
- `governance_epochs`: id, status (active/voting/closed), 5 weight columns, vote_count, created_at, closed_at
- `governance_votes`: voter_did, epoch_id, 5 weight preferences, voted_at. UNIQUE(voter_did, epoch_id)
- `governance_audit_log`: APPEND-ONLY. id, event_type, actor_did, epoch_id, details JSONB, created_at
- `subscribers`: did (PK), first_seen, last_seen, request_count
- `jetstream_cursor`: singleton row with cursor value and updated_at

## Redis Patterns
- `feed:current` — Sorted set of post URIs by total_score (the live feed)
- `feed:snapshot:{id}` — Snapshot sorted set for pagination stability (5min TTL)
- `feed:epoch` — Current epoch ID string
- `feed:updated_at` — Timestamp of last scoring run

## Migration Order
1. `001_initial_schema.sql` — posts, engagements, social_graph, subscribers, cursor
2. `002_scoring_tables.sql` — post_scores with full decomposition
3. `003_governance_tables.sql` — epochs, votes, audit_log
4. `004_transparency_tables.sql` — feed_snapshots, transparency_metrics
